{
  "policy": {
    "name": "alb-http-no-redirect-to-https",
    "resource": "aws.app-elb",
    "description": "Detect ALBs listening on port 80 without redirect to HTTPS (443).\nSecurity risk: Unencrypted HTTP traffic vulnerable to interception.\n",
    "filters": [
      {
        "type": "listener",
        "key": "Protocol",
        "value": "HTTP"
      },
      {
        "type": "listener",
        "key": "DefaultActions[0].Type",
        "value": "redirect",
        "op": "ne"
      },
      {
        "or": [
          {
            "type": "listener",
            "key": "DefaultActions[0].RedirectConfig.Protocol",
            "value": "HTTPS",
            "op": "ne"
          },
          {
            "type": "listener",
            "key": "DefaultActions[0].RedirectConfig",
            "value": "absent"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "actions": [
      {
        "type": "notify",
        "template": "default.html",
        "priority_header": "2",
        "subject": "\u26a0\ufe0f ALB HTTP Port 80 Without HTTPS Redirect - {{ region }}",
        "violation_desc": "**Application Load Balancer Not Redirecting HTTP to HTTPS**\n\n**Load Balancer:** {{ resource.LoadBalancerName }}\n**ARN:** {{ resource.LoadBalancerArn }}\n**DNS:** {{ resource.DNSName }}\n**Scheme:** {{ resource.Scheme }}\n\n**Risk:** Allows unencrypted HTTP traffic, vulnerable to man-in-the-middle attacks.\n\n**Remediation:**\n```bash\n# Add redirect rule from HTTP to HTTPS\naws elbv2 modify-listener \\\n  --listener-arn <listener-arn> \\\n  --default-actions Type=redirect,RedirectConfig='{Protocol=HTTPS,Port=443,StatusCode=HTTP_301}'\n```\n",
        "to": [
          "security-team@company.com"
        ],
        "transport": {
          "type": "sqs",
          "queue": "https://sqs.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/172327596604/custodian-mailer-queue"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "version": "0.9.47",
